data.meta_description: Imperial Noble Consort Keshun, of the Manchu Bordered Red Banner Tatara clan, was a consort of the Guangxu Emperor. She was five years his junior. She was known as to foreigners as the Pearl Concubine. Legend has it that she was drowned in a well on the orders of Empress Dowager Cixi. Wikipedia Born: 27 February 1876 Died: 15 August 1900, Forbidden City, Beijing, China Spouse: Guangxu Emperor ​ ​(m. 1889⁠–⁠1900)​ House: Tatara (他他拉; by birth); Aisin Gioro (by marriage) Siblings: Consort Jin
